# Testing Rules

Every new Python module in `src/` must have a corresponding test file in `tests/`.
Test file naming: if `src/channels/email.py` exists, then `tests/channels/test_email.py` must exist.

Testing framework: pytest only.
Never use unittest directly.
Every new function that contains logic must have at least one test.
No implementation is complete without a test scaffold.

Use pytest-asyncio for async functions.
Use pytest fixtures for database and Redis setup — never hardcode connection strings in tests.
After changes, run the hygiene sweep in `bus-hygiene.mdc` and flag doc or dependency gaps.
